  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Cool that we are tackling this one.\n\n![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/123822/11032551/b69df1ec-86dc-11e5-8a9c-2f260339ade4.png)\n\n^^^ Is the gif from @pixelastic still accurate? As for the menu (or the whole webpage), it looks really weird that the text is passing below in full transparency.\n\nI know that's a detail but I guess everyone on mobile will stumble on it and their first impression will somehow be different than if it was done in a different manner.\n\nCan we put an opaque background behind \"instantsearch.js\" so that it's not doing this?\n",
